The Telegraph - Calcutta : Metro

 Good Morning

 Hello It's Monday, April 25, 2005

 Book bazaar

 Book Bazaar at Nandan-Bangla Akademi complex.

 In aid

 An art auction in aid of charity and a fashion show of Bibi Russell?s creations at Oberoi Grand, 7.30 pm. By invitation only. 

 Visit

 An interactive session with Rajasthan chief minister Vasundhara Raje, organised by Rajasthan Foundation, at ITC Sonar Bangla, 2.30 pm. By invitation only.

 Launch

 An event titled Buddhism ? the path to Peace, Tranquility? and Nirvana will be launched by Wanna Perngmark, consul-general of Thailand, at Oxford Bookstore, 6.30 pm. An exhibition of Thakalis depicting imaginary form of five Buddhas will be opened. Talks on ?Buddhism and Youth Today?and recitations of verses from the Dhammapada will follow.

 Lenswork

 Tracing the Silk Route and Beyond Impressions of the Unknown, a joint exhibition of photographs by Ute Mitra and paintings by Badal Das will be inaugurated at Gorky Sadan, 6 pm.

 Theatre

 Saajish and Indersabha, plays in Hindi by Trinita Society and RNL Force, respectively, at Bharatiyam, Salt Lake, 6.30 pm.




